# Auth & Session Rules

## Session Shape
- Session is extended in `global.d.ts` — add new session fields there, not inline.
- Available session fields: `isLoggedIn: boolean`, `user: UserDocument`.
- Always call `req.session.save()` before redirecting after mutating session state.

## Auth Flow
- Login lives in `controllers/auth.controller.ts` + `routes/auth.routes.ts`.
- `postLogin` finds or creates a user by hardcoded id, sets session, then redirects.
- `getLogout` destroys the session and redirects to `/`.

## Middleware
- `req.user` is populated for every request in `app.ts` middleware via `UserModel.findById`.
- Do not duplicate user-loading logic in controllers — use `req.user` directly.

## Do Not
- Do not store raw passwords; this project currently has no hashing — do not add plain-text password comparisons either.
- Do not bypass `req.session.save()` before a redirect; missing it causes lost session state.

